metadata.name: Kopi? Teh? Or Mee? 1
metadata.description:
This is a play on the infamous term; a Singaporean version of "Coffee, tea or me?"

Coffee, also known as 'kopi', are often found packed in plastic bags which was helpful for dabao-ing kopi while on the way to your next destination.

While tea, affectionately called 'teh' in Singapore, is served in beautiful floral vintage cups at Kopitiams.

For 'mee', I chose to draw Hokkien Mee, a noodle dish decked with amazing sotong rings, fresh prawns, chilli paste, and zesty lime.

Created by Laugh And Belly, 2022.
